result.execSummary:
The defendant Leslie A Gilbert was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Disorderly Conduct [Modifiers: Domestic Abuse Incident], a class B misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 947.01(1).
  • Resisting or Obstructing an Officer, a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 946.41(1).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

miscConds.notes: Conditions pertain to both counts: Defendant to have no contact with J.L., complete psychological evaluation and any recommended treatment. Submit DNA sample.

Cases heard: 15CF110 & 15CF92, Defendant Leslie A Gilbert in court with attorney Ronald Gabriel Benavides.  Clifford Chase Burdon appeared for the State of Wisconsin. Amended Complaints filed; readings waived. Court went over the rights & elements. Defendant pled no contest to count one & two in 15CF92 and Count 4 in 15CF110. Court found defendant guilty, entered judgment, sentence withheld, 2 yr. probation in both cases. In 15CF92, conds: $543 and $243 costs. In 15CF110, $443 costs. In both cases, no contact J.L., psychological evaluation and treatment. DNA sample to be submitted. Jail credit to be determined by stipulation. All other cts. read in and dismissed.
